<p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-05-02-0450" class="document">TJs response to this letter, 5 Apr. 1781</a>; Callaway anticipated the Assemblys action on the draft and also the Councils determination (see <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ William W. Hening, &lt;i&gt;The Statutes at Large; Being a Collection of All the Laws of Virginia&lt;/i&gt; ]">Hening,</span> <span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">x</span>, 3935; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Council of the State of Virginia&lt;/i&gt;, ed. H. R. McIlwaine ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Va. Council Jour.</span></span>, <span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">ii</span>, 316; and Dixon &amp; Nicolsons invoice for printing, preceding, note 3).</p></div>
